article.headline: Wofford 69, Chattanooga 66
article.story: CHATTANOOGA, Tenn. -- Noah Dahlman scored 24 points and had 10 rebounds as Wofford defeated Chattanooga 69-66 on Thursday night. Chattanooga (4-10, 0-3 Southern Conference) led 40-27 with 1:54 left in the first half on a 3-pointer by Ty Patterson, before going 9-for-24 in the second. Wofford (5-6, 1-1) took a 47-46 lead with 11:21 to play on two Dahlman free throws, but the Mocs went on a 7-2 run for a 53-49 lead with 8:07 on a 3-pointer by Paterson. The Terriers reclaimed the lead for good, 59-57, on a Jason Dawson 3-pointer with 5 minutes left. Tim Johnson and Dawson added 11 points apiece for Wofford, which outrebounded the Mocs 37-34. Chattanooga came into the game with a plus-10.4 rebounding advantage over their last five games. Kevin Goffney led the Mocs with 19 points and Nicchaeus Doaks added 13 points and 10 rebounds. Patterson chipped in 14 points.
